    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.73/111</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-13T17:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President of Brazil and Minister of Public Works have signed concession giving
                    Central &amp; South American Telegraph Co. right <pb facs="0161" n="49"
                        xml:id="pg_49"/> to lay submarine cables as desired. This assures us cable
                    communication between the United States and Brazil over an all-American line and
                    breaks British monopoly. Decree will be published shortly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
